Abstract = {Einkorn (Triticum monococcum) was the first domesticated wheat species,
   and was central to the birth of agriculture and the Neolithic Revolution
   in the Fertile Crescent around 10,000 years ago(1,2). Here we generate
   and analyse 5.2-Gb genome assemblies for wild and domesticated einkorn,
